//! glow/lower_bartis.rye — lower a thin `|=` bartis gate to runnable `.rye` (STOA100–107).
//!
//! Identity gate: `|=  sample=@u32` / `sample` — takes u32 and returns it.
//! Call body: `|=  sample=@u32` / `%-  <gate>  sample` — closed demos:
//!   double → *% 2 (STOA103) · inc → +% 1 · dec → -% 1 (STOA104).
//! STOA100: baked demo sample 5; identity exits 0 when bartis_gate(5) == 5.
//! STOA101: argv sample path — main reads one decimal `@u32` and checks the body result.
//! STOA105: TAME tidy — assert · u32 · append_print · split emitters.
//! STOA107: nest/type surface — non-`@u32` sample refuses `SampleDoesNotNest`.
//! STOA109 / STOA122: named molds `amount-mold` · `count-mold` lower as `@u32`.
//! STOA123: `kind-mold` identity lowers as `KindMold` enum · baked `.mint`.
//! STOA124: `xact-mold` identity lowers as `XactMold` union · baked `.mint` amount 5.
//! STOA125: `xfer-mold` identity lowers as `XferMold` union · baked `.mint` from 5 amount 3.
//! STOA126: `pair-mold` identity lowers as `PairMold` struct · baked from 5 amount 3.
//! STOA134: `triple-mold` identity lowers as `TripleMold` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1.
//! STOA135: `quad-mold` identity lowers as `QuadMold` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2.
//! STOA136: `triple-mold` call body `%-  flip` → TripleMold swap · baked 5/3/1 → 3/5/1.
//! STOA137: `quad-mold` call body `%-  flip` → QuadMold swap · baked 5/3/1/2 → 3/5/1/2.
//! STOA138: `penta-mold` identity lowers as `PentaMold` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2 memo 7.
//! STOA139: `penta-mold` call body `%-  flip` → PentaMold swap · baked 5/3/1/2/7 → 3/5/1/2/7.
//! STOA140: `hexa-mold` identity lowers as `HexaMold` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2 memo 7 tag 4.
//! STOA141: `hexa-mold` call body `%-  flip` → HexaMold swap · baked 5/3/1/2/7/4 → 3/5/1/2/7/4.
//! STOA142: `hepta-mold` identity lowers as `HeptaMold` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2 memo 7 tag 4 to 6.
//! STOA143: `hepta-mold` call body `%-  flip` → HeptaMold swap · baked 5/3/1/2/7/4/6 → 3/5/1/2/7/4/6.
//! STOA144: `octa-mold` identity lowers as `OctaMold` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2 memo 7 tag 4 to 6 via 8.
//! STOA145: `octa-mold` call body `%-  flip` → OctaMold swap · baked 5/3/1/2/7/4/6/8 → 3/5/1/2/7/4/6/8.
//! STOA146: `nona-mold` identity lowers as `NonaMold` struct · baked from 5 amount 3 fee 1 nonce 2 memo 7 tag 4 to 6 via 8 ref 9.
//! STOA147: `nona-mold` call body `%-  flip` → NonaMold swap · baked 5/3/1/2/7/4/6/8/9 → 3/5/1/2/7/4/6/8/9.
//! STOA127: `kind-mold` call body `%-  flip` → KindMold switch · baked `.mint` → `.send`.
//! STOA128: `xact-mold` call body `%-  flip` → XactMold switch · baked mint/5 → `.send`.
//! STOA129: `xfer-mold` call body `%-  flip` → XferMold switch · baked mint/5/3 → `.send`.
//! STOA131: `pair-mold` call body `%-  flip` → PairMold swap · baked 5/3 → 3/5.
//! STOA132: `amount-mold` argv identity — generator beside fixture (u32-shaped named mold).
//! STOA133: `count-mold` argv identity — twin generator beside fixture.
//! Gate function named `bartis_gate` to avoid collisions with the sample face.

const std = @import("std");
const assert = std.debug.assert;
const rb = @import("rune_bartis.rye");
const nest_type = @import("nest_type.rye");

pub const LowerError = rb.ParseError || error{Overflow};

